channel.title: New Attempt at a 2009 Mustang V1.2
channel.description:
Well, my last attempt, although i felt it was good, wasnt satisfying enough after i viewed SomthingToHide's concept which blew mine out of the water.
here is a wire frame of the current model after about 1-2 hours of work. i know it needs serious improvement and i figured you would know how to improve upon it in its early stages to produce the best product. Wire frame: [IMG]http://i369.photobucket.com/albums/oo131/0xXDylanXx0/mustangstart.jpg[/img]
that should show enough of it as both halves are identical.
[B]Update[/b] Version 1.2
not alot of wireframe updated on the base, just slight modifications. added material and a start at rims, wheels, and windows. note that they are far from being finished, just prepped them a bit for the render. ignore the background. the background is just to show the gloss of the material. [IMG]http://i369.photobucket.com/albums/oo131/0xXDylanXx0/v3-1.jpg[/img] [IMG]http://i369.photobucket.com/albums/oo131/0xXDylanXx0/v3-2.jpg[/img] havent gotten around to the front yet.
Criticism is highly recommended

item.title: New Attempt at a 2009 Mustang V1.2
item.dc:creator: @dylan_0789 dylan_0789
item.description:
@dylan_0789 wrote:

[quote=“TabbyKiller, post:28, topic:313856”][quote author=dylan_0789 link=topic=410350.msg3035395#msg3035395 date=1258700503]

How do you get your squares in the spot you want it to? When ever I try it on either blender or metaseq its always uneven or out of place

my squares? can you be a little more descriptive of what you mean

Well everything is in its place and im wondering how you get every line so straight <.< hope that’s better

primitives. i used a cube and shaped it evenly. i made sure not to just randomly distort 1 verticy. clean face structure is something all modellers go for.
[/quote]
So do you estimate the segment and shape from there?[/quote]
i try to keep a generally neat wireframe. i look for ways to make sure it looks decent without moving the general structure out of line. if you model through the ‘trace’ method youl have alot more trouble with this as the trace method is ‘flawed’ in a way unless you can plan each verticy.
